Package: BayesEFA
Title: Bayesian Exploratory Factor Analysis Using 'Stan'
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: 
    person("Ricardo", "Rey-Sáez", , "ricardoreysaez95@gmail.com", role = c("aut", "cre", "cph"),
           comment = c(ORCID = "0000-0001-6739-2035"))
Description: Estimate Bayesian Exploratory Factor Analysis (EFA) models 
    using 'Stan' for full Bayesian inference. The package allows users 
    to fit unrestricted factor models without specifying any constraints 
    on the factor loading matrix. Instead, rotational indeterminacy is 
    resolved via an efficient Rotation-Sign-Permutation (RSP) alignment 
    algorithm, which recovers interpretable posterior distributions 
    during post-processing. Features include support for correlation, 
    covariance, and unstandardized factor models, flexible prior 
    specifications, and Full Information Maximum Likelihood (FIML) for 
    missing data. It also provides tools to calculate Bayesian fit 
    indices, Omega reliability estimates, and Bayesian factor scores 
    with full uncertainty quantification.
